<subSubSection id="02061C22A010D91ACEDB62D0DCE903F4" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="comments">
<paragraph id="64F410BF914E0B7036C11AA27E2722A3" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="695A5FDB3281C1B475A7122F208E014E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="52EDF5A81173CB705B37070E3A075B4E" authorityName="Lonsdale" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Ophiomyia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophiomyia capitolia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="capitolia">
<emphasis id="C7487696B901B923FA263C73D6236CD0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ophiomyia capitolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is one of the smaller Delmarva 
<taxonomicName id="07C59D58403FCA7D64528B92B1A0FEBD" authorityName="Braschnikov" authorityYear="1897" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Ophiomyia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophiomyia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A5D0D1A0F95916960FBC2D24A61E61F7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ophiomyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with a male wing length of 1.7 mm. This species also has a distinct genal process, a long fasciculus and a relatively distinct wrinkle under the eye within the cheek. Only examination of the male genitalia can provide reliable identification of this species (see key).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
